cs.CR, cs.MM, cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.DS

The paper deals with the challenges of decentralized data storage for multimedia streaming, which falls under the categories of computer security (cs.CR), multimedia (cs.MM), distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper proposes a novel integration of data compression, immutable off-chain data storage, and a new consensus protocol, which involves aspects of security, multimedia processing, distributed computing, networking, and data structures. Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.CR and cs.MM, followed by cs.DC, cs.NI, and cs.DS.
